<HEADLINE>
COA PROMOTES 2007 TREE-PLANTING MONTH
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Taipei,  Jan. 30 (CNA) 01/30/07  20:12:39 (By Y.F. Low)
</P>
<P>
The Council of Agriculture (COA) announced Tuesday the start of a
series of events promoting this year's tree-planting month.
</P>
<P>
Tree-planting month begins every year in Taiwan on Feb. 4 or Feb.
5, the date marked as Beginning of Spring. The festival usually
runs through March 12, which is celebrated as Arbor Day.
</P>
<P>
COA officials said council's  Forestry Bureau is accepting
applications from local communities to hold tree-planting
activities, with the number of participating communities expected
to reach 500 this year.
</P>
<P>
In addition,  the council is inviting local residents and
businesses to plant trees on designated, idle government-owned
land, farmland, coastal areas and vacant areas of government
agencies and schools, the officials said.
</P>
<P>
They said the council will also launch a Web site featuring tree-
planting month, which will provide instructions on tree planting
and host a design contest for cards commemorating tree-planting
month.
</P>
<P>
Officials said the COA will continue its reforestation efforts
this year, with the goal of planting a total of 30 hectares of
trees on the outlying islands and 500 hectares of trees on plains
around Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the council plans to restore 750 hectares of barren
land and 70 hectares of coastal forest, they added.
</P>
